title: Hokusai The Great Wave Keychain
description:
Key Chain developed from Katsushika Hokusai’s The Great Wave, 1820-33, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

This artwork is the most famous image from the set the “Great Wave” (Kanagawa oki nami ura), in which a diminutive Mount Fuji can be seen in the distance under the crest of a giant wave.

A great gift for yourself of a friend.

  • Dimensions of charm: 1.625 x .125 in.
  • Materials: Brass with colored enamel
